 {"id":"br-r37-c1-cujmq","title":"parity: VF2 GraphMatcher/DiGraphMatcher/MultiGraphMatcher classes missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.isomorphism exposes GraphMatcher, DiGraphMatcher, MultiGraphMatcher, MultiDiGraphMatcher classes for the classical VF2 algorithm with rich API: subgraph_is_isomorphic(), subgraph_isomorphisms_iter(), match(), candidate_pairs_iter(), semantic_feasibility(), syntactic_feasibility(), initialize(). fnx exposes only the top-level functions (is_isomorphic, vf2pp_*) but no Matcher classes. Add wrapper classes that delegate to nx.algorithms.isomorphism via _networkx_graph_for_parity, exporting as fnx.GraphMatcher etc.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T07:30:43.669346473Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:18:29.924704555Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:18:29.922845114Z","close_reason":"Completed in 742c813","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-d967f","title":"parity: approximation treewidth/steiner/dominating/max-cut/ramsey/densest wrappers missing (10 functions)","description":"After the TSP family (br-8vobd), 10 more approximation algorithms remain unexposed: treewidth_min_degree(G), treewidth_min_fill_in(G), steiner_tree(G, terminal_nodes, weight, method), min_edge_dominating_set(G), min_maximal_matching(G), min_weighted_dominating_set(G, weight), one_exchange(G, initial_cut, seed, weight), randomized_partitioning(G, seed, p, weight), ramsey_R2(G), densest_subgraph(G, iterations, method). All are pure heuristics with no Rust counterpart — add wrappers via the existing _call_networkx_approximation_for_parity helper, export at top-level, add to __all__ under the approximation section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T19:34:18.988742298Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T19:57:48.971397375Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T19:57:48.969471288Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 66ec413: 10 approximation wrappers (treewidth_min_degree/min_fill_in, steiner_tree, min_edge_dominating_set, min_maximal_matching, min_weighted_dominating_set, one_exchange, randomized_partitioning, ramsey_R2, densest_subgraph). All verified against nx on K5/C6/P6/K6/C7/BA20 graphs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-f64cy","title":"parity: pagerank silently falls back to unweighted when weight attr is missing","description":"fnx.pagerank(G, weight='nope') on a graph whose edges lack a 'nope' attribute returns the unweighted result instead of raising. NetworkX defaults the missing attribute to 1 (treated as edge weight 1) — semantically same as unweighted but only when ALL edges lack the key. fnx behavior is similar but should be verified against nx for partial-attribute graphs (some edges weighted, others missing). Add parity test that builds a graph where half the edges have weight, half don't, and asserts fnx and nx agree to 1e-9.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T08:26:41.408497679Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:11:17.258068772Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:11:17.256114832Z","close_reason":"Verified parity. fnx.pagerank already matches nx exactly on per-edge default-1 fallback for missing weight attributes — no code fix needed. Landed tests/python/test_pagerank_weight_parity.py (commit 400eefe) with 6 cases pinning the contract: all-weighted, weight='nope' (all missing), partial weights (half missing), weight=None, DiGraph partial, plus a sanity check that asymmetric weights produce a non-trivial pagerank delta vs unweighted (proving the implementation isn't in a hidden global fallback path).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-fuuor","title":"parity: random_labeled_rooted_forest stray q arg + tutte_polynomial positional x/y","description":"Two stale signatures: random_labeled_rooted_forest(n, q=None, seed=None) carried a stray q from random_unlabeled_rooted_forest (nx is just (n, *, seed=None)). tutte_polynomial(G, x=None, y=None) accepted x/y positionally as a numeric-evaluation extension; nx is (G,) only. Drop-in callers writing for nx and trying tutte_polynomial(G, 1, 1) had the call work on fnx but raise TypeError on nx. Aligned: rrf drops q (replaced by random_unlabeled_rooted_forest forwarder), tutte_polynomial makes x/y KEYWORD_ONLY. Also fixed tutte_polynomial recursion to use kwarg form internally. 6 parity tests freeze the contract.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T04:36:37.664864574Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T04:36:37.664864574Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-g915s","title":"parity: greedy_color rejects callable strategy despite docstring claiming str or function","description":"fnx.greedy_color(G, strategy=callable) raises TypeError: argument strategy: function object is not an instance of str. The docstring claims str or function but the implementation only accepts strings (passes them straight to _raw_greedy_color). NetworkX accepts both str and callable. Fix: route callable strategies through nx via _call_networkx_for_parity, similar to interchange=True. Discovered while shipping br-75r94 (strategy_* wrappers).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-25T23:49:39.924775622Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T00:09:39.089203090Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T00:09:39.087297771Z","close_reason":"Shipped in f02d0f6: greedy_color routes callable strategies through networkx (interchange=True path). Verified on C6 with string, fnx.strategy_*, nx.coloring.strategy_*, and lambda strategies — all produce identical colorings to nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-h41f2","title":"parity: isomorphism match helper functions missing","description":"NetworkX exposes categorical_node_match, categorical_edge_match, categorical_multiedge_match, numerical_node_match, numerical_edge_match, numerical_multiedge_match, generic_node_match, generic_edge_match, and generic_multiedge_match from networkx.algorithms.isomorphism. FrankenNetworkX does not export these helpers, so callback construction for GraphMatcher and is_isomorphic differs. Add wrappers delegating to networkx.algorithms.isomorphism and parity tests covering node/edge/multiedge helper behavior.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:19:58.209906853Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:24:21.965842231Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:24:21.963986187Z","close_reason":"Completed in bc5cd31","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-hq5pq","title":"parity: connectivity minimum_st_edge_cut missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.minimum_st_edge_cut(G, s, t, flow_func=None, auxiliary=None, residual=None) returns minimum st edge cut. Not exposed by franken_networkx (only minimum_edge_cut and minimum_st_node_cut exist). Add Python wrapper delegating to networkx and export at top-level.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:59:43.139262003Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:15:05.326488163Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:15:05.324637730Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in fnx — top-level export matches nx.connectivity exactly. Landed tests/python/test_connectivity_parity_extras.py (commit 3765516) with 37 cases freezing the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-j6qpf","title":"parity: draw_bipartite signature divergence — fnx requires top_nodes positionally, nx accepts only **kwargs","description":"fnx.draw_bipartite has signature (G, top_nodes, pos=None, **kwds) where top_nodes is a required positional arg, but networkx.drawing.nx_pylab.draw_bipartite has (G, **kwargs). Drop-in calls like nx.draw_bipartite(G) work in nx but fnx raises TypeError missing positional argument top_nodes. Fix: align signature to (G, **kwargs) and pull top_nodes out of kwargs (or compute it via bipartite_sets if absent), so fnx accepts the same call shape as nx.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T04:28:46.975023293Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T04:33:37.004948628Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-lmviu","title":"parity: add_path/add_cycle/add_star keyword parameter names","description":"NetworkX exposes add_path(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_path, **attr), add_cycle(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_cycle, **attr), and add_star(G_to_add_to, nodes_for_star, **attr). FNX currently names these parameters G and nodes, so documented keyword calls like fnx.add_path(G_to_add_to=G, nodes_for_path=[1,2]) raise TypeError. Align the public signatures while preserving positional behavior and add parity tests.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T06:20:06.172080189Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T06:23:19.168859030Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T06:23:19.167009410Z","close_reason":"Completed in 92bae80","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-lz7u6","title":"parity: connectivity bridge_components missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.bridge_components(G) returns 2-edge-connected components after removing bridges. Not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrapper delegating to nx.algorithms.connectivity.bridge_components via _networkx_graph_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:44:53.163889437Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:14:43.967902315Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:14:43.966070217Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in fnx — top-level export matches nx.connectivity exactly. Landed tests/python/test_connectivity_parity_extras.py (commit 3765516) with 37 cases freezing the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-m4msi","title":"parity: utils.random_sequence powerlaw_sequence + zipf_rv + cumulative_distribution + is_valid_tree_degree_sequence (4 functions)","description":"Four random-sequence utilities from networkx.utils.random_sequence not surfaced by franken_networkx: powerlaw_sequence(n, exponent=2.0, seed=None), zipf_rv(alpha, xmin=1, seed=None), cumulative_distribution(distribution), is_valid_tree_degree_sequence(degree_sequence). These are used by stochastic graph generators and degree-sequence sanity checks. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level and adding to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T21:59:39.857059179Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T03:18:46.320103675Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T03:18:46.318235318Z","close_reason":"Already implemented. powerlaw_sequence/zipf_rv/cumulative_distribution exposed at fnx top level matching nx.utils bit-for-bit when seeded; discrete_sequence on fnx.utils; is_valid_tree_degree_sequence is fnx-only ((bool, reason) tuple). Landed tests/python/test_random_sequence_parity.py (commit d2ed994) with 89 cases freezing the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
